### Store plugin and item directories in variables ###
ITEM_DIR="$HOME/.config/sketchybar/items"       # Directory where the items are configured
PLUGIN_DIR="$HOME/.config/sketchybar/plugins"   # Directory where all the plugin scripts are stored

### Define defult font ###
FONT="Monocraft" # Needs to have Regular, Bold, Semibold, Heavy and Black variants

### Padding ###
PADDINGS=3  # All elements use this padidng
###
### Setting up the general bar appearance and default values ###
sketchybar --bar     height=50                                                     \
                     corner_radius=14                                              \
                     border_width=0                                                \
                     margin=95                                                     \
                     blur_radius=0                                                 \
                     position=top                                                  \
                     padding_left=4                                                \
                     padding_right=4                                               \
                     color=0xff1a1c26                                              \
                     topmost=off                                                   \
                     sticky=on                                                     \
                     font_smoothing=off                                            \
                     y_offset=-100                                                    \
                     notch_width=0                                                 \
                                                                                   \
           --default drawing=on                                                    \
                     updates=when_shown                                            \
                     icon.padding_left=$PADDINGS                                   \
                     icon.padding_right=$PADDINGS                                  \
                     label.padding_left=$PADDINGS                                  \
                     label.padding_right=$PADDINGS                                 \
                     background.padding_right=$PADDINGS                            \
                     background.padding_left=$PADDINGS                             \

sketchybar --animate sin 30 --bar y_offset=-100 y_offset=9

### Left ###
. "$ITEM_DIR/arch_menu.sh" # arch logo
. "$ITEM_DIR/system.sh"    # resources monitor
. "$ITEM_DIR/spotify.sh"   # spotify widget
# . "$ITEM_DIR/clipboard.sh"   # spotify widget

### Center ###
. "$ITEM_DIR/spaces.sh"    # workspaces

### Right ###
. "$ITEM_DIR/time.sh"      # time
. "$ITEM_DIR/updates.sh"   # updates
. "$ITEM_DIR/sound.sh"     # sound
. "$ITEM_DIR/battery.sh"   # battery
. "$ITEM_DIR/playing.sh"   # playing on spotify

echo "sketchybar configuation loaded.."
sketchybarrc.purpose: This file, named sketchybarrc, is used to configure SketchyBar, a macOS system status bar application. It sets up the appearance, behavior, and plugins of the bar, including its dimensions, font, padding, and position.
sketchybarrc.content_summary: The file defines variables for item and plugin directories, a default font, and padding values. It also sets up the general bar appearance, including height, corner radius, border width, margin, color, topmost, sticky, font smoothing, y_offset, notch_width, and animations. The file then loads various plugins for the left, center, and right sections of the bar, including items for the arch logo, system resources monitor, Spotify widget, workspaces, time, updates, sound, battery, playing on Spotify.

plugins/mem.sh.content:
#!/usr/bin/env bash

getPrecentage=$(TARGET_PATH="."
top -l 1 | grep -E "^CPU" | grep -Eo '[^[:space:]]+%' | head -1 | sed 's/3\(.\)$/\1/' | cut -d "." -f1)

getMB=$(TARGET_PATH="."
top -l1 | awk '/PhysMem/ {print $2}')

precentage=$(echo $getPrecentage)
MB=$(echo $getMB)

sketchybar --set $NAME icon="" label="$precentage%"
plugins/mem.sh.purpose: This file is a SketchyBar plugin script that monitors CPU usage and memory usage on a Linux system and displays the information in the SketchyBar interface.
plugins/mem.sh.content_summary: The script uses the top command to gather CPU and memory usage data, processes the data to extract the percentage of CPU usage and the amount of memory usage in megabytes, and then sets the SketchyBar's icon, label, and values based on the gathered data.

    set playerState to player state as string
end tell
playerState
' | grep -q 'playing'; then

  else

  fi
}

plugins/space.sh.content:
#!/usr/bin/env sh

args=()
if [ "$NAME" != "space_template" ]; then
  args+=(--set $NAME label=$NAME \
                     icon.highlight=$SELECTED)
fi

sketchybar -m --animate tanh 0 "${args[@]}"

if [ "$SELECTED" = "true" ]; then
  args+=(--set spaces_$DID.label label=${NAME#"spaces_$DID."} \
         --set $NAME icon.background.y_offset=0               )
fi

WIN=$(yabai -m query --spaces --space $SID | jq '.windows[0]')
HAS_WINDOWS_OR_IS_SELECTED="true"
if [ "$WIN" = "null" ] && [ "$SELECTED" = "false" ];then
  HAS_WINDOWS_OR_IS_SELECTED="false"
fi

if [ "$HAS_WINDOWS_OR_IS_SELECTED" = "true" ]; then
   icon=
   iconfont="Font Awesome 6 Free:Solid:15.0"
   offset="1"
   iconcolor=0xff7aa1f7
else
   icon=⬤
   iconcolor=0xff583794
fi

if [ "$SELECTED" = "true" ]; then
  icon=
  iconfont="Pacman-Dots:Regular:15.5"
  offset="1"
fi


sketchybar --set $NAME icon.highlight=$SELECTED icon.y_offset=$offset icon.font="$iconfont" icon.color=$iconcolor icon=$icon

plugins/clipboard.py.content:
#!python3
import json
import subprocess

class Clipboard:
  def __init__(self, file: str) -> None:
      self.file = file
      try: 
          with open(self.file, 'r') as openfile:
              json_object = json.load(openfile)
      except: 
          json_object = { "clipboard": [] }
      self.storage = json_object

  def write_to_clipboard(self) -> None:
      json_object = json.dumps(self.storage, indent=4)
      with open(self.file, "w") as outfile:
          outfile.write(json_object)

  def add_to_clipboard(self) -> bool:
      clip = subprocess.check_output("pbpaste").decode('utf-8').strip()
      if clip not in self.storage["clipboard"]:
          if len(self.storage["clipboard"]) < 5:
              self.storage["clipboard"].append(clip)
          else:
              self.storage["clipboard"].pop(0)
              self.storage["clipboard"].append(clip)
          return True
      return False

  def draw_clipboard(self) -> None:
      options: list[str] = []
      if len(self.storage["clipboard"]) == 0:
          options += [
              'sketchybar',
              '-m',
              "--remove", 
              '/clipboard.template.[0-5]/',
              '--add',
              'item',
              f'clipboard.template.0', 
              'popup.clipboard',
              '--set',
              f'clipboard.template.0',
              'icon="Clipboard: "',
              'label="nothing has been copied"'
          ]
          subprocess.call(options)
      for clip in range(0, len(self.storage["clipboard"])):
          options += [
              'sketchybar',
              '-m',
              "--remove", 
              '/clipboard.template.[0-5]/',
              '--add',
              'item',
              f'clipboard.template.{clip}', 
              'popup.clipboard',
              '--set',
              f'clipboard.template.{clip}',
              'icon=◆',
              'icon.font="JetBrains Mono:Regular:14.0"',
              f'label={self.storage["clipboard"][clip]}',
              '--set',
              f'clipboard.template.{clip}',
               f"""click_script=`echo '{self.storage["clipboard"][clip]}' | pbcopy` """
              'drawing=on',
              'label.width=120',
              'background.corner_radius=12',
              'background.padding_left=12',
              'background.padding_right=12',
              'background.drawing=off'
          ]
          try:
              subprocess.call(options)
          except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e:
              print ("write_to_clipboard.ERROR: ", e.output)

if __name__ == "__main__":
  clipboard = Clipboard("/Users/itaysharir/.config/.clipboard_storage.json")
  if clipboardHasChanged := clipboard.add_to_clipboard():
      clipboard.write_to_clipboard()
      clipboard.draw_clipboard()

spotify/back.sh.purpose: The purpose of this file is to control the Spotify application on macOS, specifically to navigate to the previous track.

spotify/artist.sh.content:
osascript -e 'tell application "System Events"
        set processList to (name of every process)
end tell

if (processList contains "Spotify") is true then
        tell application "Spotify"
                set artistName to artist of current track
                set trackName to name of current track
                set symbol to "◻︎"
                set col to "red"

                if player state is playing then
                        set symbol to "▹"
                        set col to "green"
                end if

                return artistName
        end tell
end if'
spotify/artist.sh.purpose: The given file is a script written in AppleScript for SketchyBar, a macOS system status bar utility. Its purpose is to display the name of the current artist and track playing in Spotify, along with a symbol indicating the player state (playing or paused).
spotify/artist.sh.content_summary: This script checks if Spotify is running, then retrieves the current artist and track name, and sets a symbol and color based on the player state. If Spotify is playing, the symbol is a play icon and the color is green. If Spotify is paused, the symbol is a solid square and the color is red.

spotify/forward.sh.purpose: The purpose of this file is to control the Spotify application and skip to the next track using AppleScript.
spotify/forward.sh.content_summary: The file contains a command that uses the osascript utility to execute an AppleScript command, which in turn tells the Spotify application to move to the next track.

spotify/playpause.sh.content:
osascript -e 'using terms from application "Spotify"
	tell application "Spotify" to playpause
end using terms from'
spotify/playpause.sh.purpose: The purpose of this file is to control the playback of Spotify using AppleScript on macOS.
spotify/playpause.sh.content_summary: This file contains a command that uses the osascript utility to interact with the Spotify application, specifically to toggle the play/pause state of the currently playing track.

spotify/song.sh.content:

        set processList to (name of every process)
end tell

if (processList contains "Spotify") is true then
        tell application "Spotify"
                set artistName to artist of current track

                if player state is playing then

end if'

#!/usr/bin/env sh

POPUP_CLICK_SCRIPT="sketchybar --set \$NAME popup.drawing=toggle"

sketchybar --add item clipboard left                        \
         --set clipboard script="python3 $PLUGIN_DIR/clipboard.py" \
                         updates=on                             \
                         update_freq=30                    \
                         icon=                          \
                         icon.font="Font Awesome 6 Free:Solid:15.0"      \
                         icon.color=0xffd3bd97                      \
                         background.padding_right=8            \
                         background.padding_left=8            \
                         click_script="python3 $PLUGIN_DIR/clipboard.py && $POPUP_CLICK_SCRIPT" \
         --add item clipboard.template left popup.clipboard \

items/spaces.sh.content:
#!/usr/bin/env sh

export SPACE_CLICK_SCRIPT="yabai -m space --focus \$SID 2>/dev/null"

sketchybar --add   space          space_template center                \
           --set   space_template icon.color=0xff583794              \
                                  icon.highlight_color=0xffe0af68    \
                                  label.drawing=off                  \
                                  drawing=on                        \
                                  updates=on                         \
                                  associated_display=1               \
                                  label.font="$FONT:Black:10.0"      \
                                  icon.font="Pacman-Dots:Regular:9.0"        \
                                  background.corner_radius=33       \
                                  background.color=0xff252630        \
                                  background.height=33               \
                                  click_script="$SPACE_CLICK_SCRIPT" \
                                  ignore_association=on              \
                                  icon.padding_left=0               \
                                  icon.padding_right=64               \
                                  background.padding_right=-24              \
                                  background.padding_left=-24              \
                                                                     \
           --clone spaces_1.idle  space_template                     \
           --set   spaces_1.idle  associated_space=1                 \
                                  icon=⬤                            \
                                  script="$PLUGIN_DIR/space.sh"      \
                                  icon.padding_left=8               \
                                                                     \
           --clone spaces_1.misc  space_template                     \
           --set   spaces_1.misc  associated_space=2                 \
                                  icon=⬤                           \
                                  script="$PLUGIN_DIR/space.sh"      \
                                                                     \
           --clone spaces_1.doc   space_template                     \
           --set   spaces_1.doc   associated_space=3                 \
                                  icon=⬤                           \
                                  drawing=on                         \
                                  script="$PLUGIN_DIR/space.sh"      \
                                                                     \
           --clone spaces_1.help  space_template                     \
           --set   spaces_1.help  associated_space=4                 \
                                  icon=⬤                           \
                                  script="$PLUGIN_DIR/space.sh"      \
                                                                     \
           --clone spaces_1.music space_template                     \
           --set   spaces_1.music associated_space=5                 \
                                  icon=⬤                           \
                                  script="$PLUGIN_DIR/space.sh"      \
                                                                        \
           --clone spaces_2.nine  space_template                     \
           --set   spaces_2.nine  associated_space=6                 \
                                  icon=⬤                          \
                                  script="$PLUGIN_DIR/space.sh"      \
                                  icon.padding_right=0               \
                                                                     \
           --add   bracket        spaces_1                           \
                                  spaces_1.label                     \
                                  spaces_1.idle                      \
                                  spaces_1.misc                      \
                                  spaces_1.doc                       \
                                  spaces_1.help                      \
                                  spaces_1.music                     \
                                  spaces_1.nine                      \
                                  spaces_1.label                     \
                                  spaces_1.code                      \
                                  spaces_1.web                       \
                                  spaces_1.tex                       \
                                  spaces_1.web                       \
items/spaces.sh.purpose: This file is used to configure SketchyBar items for managing workspace (spaces) in a macOS environment, specifically using the yabai window tiling manager.
items/spaces.sh.content_summary: The file defines a space item with custom properties such as color, font, padding, and click script for focusing a specific workspace. It also clones this space item for each workspace and assigns an associated space number and icon to each clone. Finally, it adds a bracket item that groups these space items together.
